{
  "texts": [
    "Existing graph pooling computing frameworks such as Deep Graph Library (DGL) (Wang 2019a), Inspired by PyG, Tf-geometric (Hu et al. 2021) is implemented on the TensorFlow backend framework, providing TensorFlow users with a similar toolset for graph neural networks.",
    "PGL (Ma et al. 2019c) is a high-performance library specialized in graph neural networks based on the PaddlePaddle deep learning framework.",
    "It provides a rich set of graph neural network algorithms and efficient large-scale graph processing capabilities.",
    "CogDL (Cen et al. 2023) is a large-scale graph representation learning toolkit introduced by the Knowledge Engineering Research Laboratory of Tsinghua University, which provides researchers with a convenient solution for graph representation learning.",
    "NeuGraph (Ma et al. 2019d) is a graph neural network training framework that combines a data streaming system and a graph processing system, aiming to improve the training efficiency of large-scale graph neural networks."
  ]
}